laboratory_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated to 15mm with a large amount of fat stranding and small free fluid in the right paracolic gutter. An 8-mm hyperdensity at the appendiceal orifice is an appendicolith. No drainable fluid collection. No free air. Mildly distended fluid filled loops of small bowel may be a reactive ileus. The unenhanced liver, gallbladder, spleen, pancreas and bilateral adrenal glands are normal. No renal stone, hydronephrosis or contour-altering renal mass.
